## Output

Write each finding via `loom output add` against the
`findings.yaml` schema. Empty findings array = no violations.
Each finding requires:

- `title`        — short violation summary (≤ 80 chars)
- `file_line`    — `<path>:<line>` or `""` if file-wide
- `description`  — 1–2 sentences. State the violation and why
                   it matters. No restating the title verbatim.
                   No background, no enumeration of conventions.
- `fix`          — 1 sentence. Concrete remediation only — what
                   to change. No alternatives, no rationale.
- `severity`     — `Error`, `Warning`, or `Info`

Hard limit: `description` ≤ 60 words, `fix` ≤ 30 words. Reviewers
read the whole report — verbosity hides signal.

Initialise the output file once, then append findings:

    {{ vars.loom_sh }} output init {{ run.workdir }} \
        --task {{ task.id }}

    {{ vars.loom_sh }} output add {{ run.workdir }} \
        --task {{ task.id }} \
        --set findings.0.title='<short>' \
        --set findings.0.file_line='SKILL.md:42' \
        --set findings.0.description='<full reason>' \
        --set findings.0.fix='<concrete change>' \
        --set findings.0.severity=Error \
        --set findings.0.source={{ task.id }}

Increment the array index per finding (`findings.0`, `findings.1`,
…). If you find nothing, run `output init` only — the empty
`findings: []` is valid.

